ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, the Fe doped norepinephrine-based carbon dots was successfully prepared by a one-step microwave digestion method, and then self-assembled with PB to obtain Fe,NA-CDs/PB. Finally, the gold nanoparticles (AuNPs) nanozymes sensor was synthesized by utilizing the reducing properties of CDs. The Fe,NA-CDs/PB and AuNPs with SERS and POD-like activities can catalyze the oxidation of the colorless ABTS and TMB to the blue ox-ABTS and ox-TMB as the SERS-active substrates. A quantitative colorimetric and SERS dual-mode sensor for Pb(II) detection was constructed by Pb(II) inhibited POD-like activities of nanozymes (
                     Scheme 1

                     ), whose linear range satisfied inspection requirements. The nanozymes was well used for the detection of Pb(II) in traditional Chinese medicine samples with good repeatability and recovery.

To examine the effect of different metal ions, including Cu2+, Fe3+, Zn2+, the POD-like activity of NA-CDs was investigated using TMB with H2O2 as substrate. The presence of Fe3+ increases the POD-like activity of NA-CDs solution. In the end, we verified the synergistic effect of FeCl3 and PB to enhance POD-like activity of nanozymes using TMB as a substrate. A steady-state kinetic reaction was carried out by varying the amount of TMB and H2O2 while keeping the concentration of the other substances constant to comprehend the catalytic mechanism of Fe,NA-CDs/PB. It is well known that value of K m expressed the relationship of substrates for the enzyme, and a higher K m value shows a weaker affinity and vice versa. The maximum rate (V max) of Fe,NA-CDs/PB nanozyme was calculated as 7.2 × 10−8 Ms−1, and K m values of nanozyme were calculated as 2.1 mM for H2O2 by UV–vis absorption measurement ( Fig. 2
A-D; Table 1
). These outcomes demonstrate the excellent adsorption capacities and a high sensitivity SERS signal intensity response of AuNPs, providing further reliable evidence of AuNPs high catalytic efficiency.
